Jubilee Party has defended its smart membership card that is set to be unveiled on Friday at Kasarani Stadium.Chairman Raphael Tuju said the card will have member&rsquo;s data, including their ID number, age, constituency and party registration number. It will also be fitted with a unique barcode.Tuju on Monday said the card allows members to make changes on their data in case the same is not reflected at first registration.&ldquo;We will be in a position to rectify errors that may lock a member from taking part in the party&rsquo;s primaries,&rdquo; the former Information minister said. He said the Sh20 card will be sold to all members as a source of revenue for JP.Tuju said the Friday event will be presided over by party leaders President Uhuru Kenyatta and Deputy President William Ruto.&ldquo;We will show members how to register using the card and use it to conduct party affairs,&rdquo; Tuju said. The former Rarieda MP said the card will help JP have credible nominations as one cannot vote twice.The Friday meeting is set to bring together aspirants for governor, senator, woman representative, MP and MCA seats as well as JP officials.Jubilee and Cord are at loggerheads over the use of a manual backup during the August 8 general election. &ldquo;We are targeting all the potential eight million voters in the country,&rdquo; the former MP said. With already ten million cards on the way, the party is expected to make Sh200 million.